synonyms: āśvine—in the month of Āśvina (September-October); padma-nābha—Padmanābha; kārtike—in the month of Kārttika (October-November); dāmodara—Dāmodara; rādhā-dāmodara—the Dāmodara of Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇī; anya—another; vrajendra-koṅara—the son of Mahārāja Nanda.
translation: "In the month of Āśvina, the predominating Deity is Padmanābha, and in Kārttika it is Dāmodara. This Dāmodara is different from Rādhā-Dāmodara, the son of Nanda Mahārāja in Vṛndāvana.
